# Create a Jenkins Freestyle Project with parameterized builds that displays a custom welcome message.

✅ Step-by-Step Guide to Create a Parameterized Jenkins Job

Step 1: Access Jenkins
Open Jenkins: http://<your-ec2-public-ip>:8080
Login with your credentials.

Step 2: Create a New Freestyle Project
Click “New Item”.
Name it: WelcomeMessageBuild.
Select “Freestyle project”.
Click OK.

Step 3: Enable Parameterized Build
On the configuration page, check “This project is parameterized”.
Click “Add Parameter” → “String Parameter”.
Fill in below deatils as:
Name: USER_NAME
Default Value: Ganga Vaishnu Reddy. Emani
Description: Enter your name

Step 4: Add Build Step
Scroll to Build section.
Click “Add build step” → “Execute shell”.
Paste the following shell script:

Step 5: Save and Run
Click “Save”.
Click “Build with Parameters”.
Enter your name or use the default.
Click “Build”.
Go to the build → Console Output to see the message.
